The John Emulators (John GBC, John NES, John SNES) are quite frankly the 
best emulators for android. Though the free "Lite" versions are fine, the 
ads are not excessive. But to eliminate ads, its very worthwhile to invest 
the $2.99. The quality of these emulators are top notch, with more features 
than you can dream of, especially the cheat code feature (Game Genie, Pro 
Action Replay, Game Shark, etc) is extremely helpful. Manual input of the 
codes are needed only once. The codes are saved for later playing. This 
allows for better hacking abilities than the auto download code options 
available on other emulators, because you can enter more codes from 
multiple sites, and not have input problems like those other emulators do. 
Copy-pasting the codes from websites works best as you don't have to try to 
memorize random letters and numbers. With Dropbox support, all of your 
games and data is saved easily and management is simple with a well 
designed user interface. I've never had any problems with any ROM not 
working, as long as the ROM is good. Its a great app that is well deserved 
an excellent reputation. Get all the John Emulators for your classic gaming 
needs! I'm waiting for John Sega Genesis!

Love this app and I'm happy to have paid for it!   However, there are a few minor GUI features that could use more options. For example, it'd be nice to be able to move and stretch the game pad and buttons at an absolute coordinate position rather than just making them bigger or smaller. Also, auto frame skip doesn't work properly in landscape mode...? And maybe a small clock in the corner so it can be used in fullscreen mode while still knowing the time. Start and Select are also abysmal at recognizing taps in landscape mode. And though just a nicety, maybe adding 4x and 8x speeds while you're at it? Oh, and a confirm prompt after pressing "Reset" would be ideal since I've accidentally pressed it when scrolling though the menu several times, losing all progress since my last save.   And if you really want to surprise users, adding GBA emulation would make this the single best app on Google Play right now. But if any of these little issues are fixed, I'm happy to rate at 5-stars.
